[graphql] Define basic GraphQL query to fetch unique identities

This commit defines a basic schema and a query to retrieve
the information stored by unique identitiesn. To ask for the
list of unique identities and their related data stored by
SortingHat, a GraphQL query would be like this:

```
{
  uidentities {
    uuid
    profile {
      name
      email
      country {
         name
      }
    }
    identities {
      id
      name
      email
      username
      source
    }
    enrollments {
      organization {
        name
      }
      start
      end
    }
  }
}
```

[graphql] Define GraphQL mutation to add organizations

The mutation 'addOrganization' allows to create a new
organization in the registry. Errors are returned in
case the organization already exists or the name is
invalid.

To add an organization a mutation query like this will
work:

  mutation addOrg {
    addOrganization(name: "Example") {
      organization {
        name
      }
    }
  }

[graphql] Define GraphQL mutation to delete organizations

The mutation 'deleteOrganization' allows to remove an
organization from the registry. Errors are returned in
case the organization does not exist.

To remove an organization a mutation query like this will
work:

  mutation delOrg {
    deleteOrganization(name: "Example") {
      organization {
        name
      }
    }
  }

[graphql] Define GraphQL mutation to add domains

The mutation 'addDomain' allows to add a domain to the
registry. Errors are returned in case the organization
where this domain added does not exist, when the domain
name is empty or when it already exists in the registry.

To add a domain a mutation query like this will work:

  mutation addDom {
    addDomain(organization: "Example", domain: "example.net") {
      domain {
        domain
        isTopDomain
        organization {
          name
        }
      }
    }
  }

[graphql] Define GraphQL mutation to delete domains

The mutation 'deleteDomain' allows to remove a domain
from the registry. Errors are returned in case the domain
does not exist.

To remove a domain, a mutation query like this will work:

  mutation delDom {
    deleteDomain(domain: "example.net") {
      domain {
        domain
        isTopDomain
      }
    }
  }
